<p> At night, the alienation of one man in a crowd gives way to the solitude of a few waiting at desolate stations for long empty trains. These are the night workers, the lovers going home from an evening out and the loveless for whom the subways represent warmth and security.<br>

<div style="text-align: right;">
''- New York Times''
</div></p>
